/imagine image of three bears - Daddy Bear, Mother Bear and Baby Bear - equipped with clothes. The bears are often shown in their cozy home, described as a wooden abode deep in the forest. The image also shows Goldilocks, the mischievous and restless girl, entering the bear's house uninvited and causing chaos.

Several pictures in the book show Goldilocks trying on a bear's chair, bed, and porridge. These scenes often include humorous images of Goldilocks, who is described as a curious and hyperactive child with blond hair.

Overall, the visuals in "Goldilocks and the Three Bears" help create the witchy and mischievous atmosphere of this classic children's story. They help add to the magic of the story and make it a fun and memorable book for children.
